{"version":3,"timestamp":"2026-02-11T01:55:35.286Z","sessions":{"26216172ff1537fb":{"agent":"claude","model":"claude-opus-4-6","prompts":[{"id":68,"timestamp":"2026-02-10T23:42:17.285Z","content":"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Add Jaeger trace export in debug mode\n\n## Context\n\nWhen debugging git-fs, the indicatif spinner output and flat log lines make it hard to understand span durations and call hierarchies. Jaeger provides a visual timeline of traces with span durations, parent-child relationships, and field values — much better for performance debugging.\n\nThe goal: when `GIT_FS_LOG` is set (ugly/debug mode), also export spans to a local Jaeger instance via OTLP. Pretty (丑) mode is unaffected.\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. Add dependencies to `Cargo.toml`\n\n```toml\nopentelemetry = \"0.29\"\nopentelemetry_sdk = { version = \"0.29\", features = [\"rt-tokio\"] }\nopentelemetry-otlp = \"0.29\"\ntracing-opentelemetry = \"0.30\"\n```\n\nModern Jaeger (v1.35+) accepts OTLP directly on port 4317, so no jaeger-specific exporter crate is needed.\n\n### 2. Modify `src/trc.rs`\n\n**Add an OpenTelemetry layer in ugly mode only.**\n\nIn `Trc::init()`, when the mode is `TrcMode::Ugly`:\n1. Initialize an OTLP span exporter targeting `http://localhost:4317`\n2. Build an `SdkTracerProvider` with the exporter and `service.name = \"git-fs\"`\n3. Create a `tracing_opentelemetry::layer()` from the tracer\n4. Add it to the registry alongside the existing reload layer + env filter\n\n**Store the `SdkTracerProvider` in `TrcHandle` for clean shutdown:**\n\n```rust\npub struct TrcHandle {\n    fmt_handle: FmtReloadHandle,\n    tracer_provider: Option<opentelemetry_sdk::trace::SdkTracerProvider>,\n}\n\nimpl Drop for TrcHandle {\n    fn drop(&mut self) {\n        if let Some(provider) = self.tracer_provider.take() {\n            if let Err(e) = provider.shutdown() {\n                eprintln!(\"Failed to shutdown OpenTelemetry tracer: {e}\");\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**`Trc::init()` ugly branch becomes:**\n\n```rust\nTrcMode::Ugly { .. } => {\n    let exporter = opentelemetry_otlp::SpanExporter::builder()\n        .with_tonic()\n        .build()?;\n    let provider = opentelemetry_sdk::trace::SdkTracerProvider::builder()\n        .with_batch_exporter(exporter)\n        .with_resource(\n            Resource::builder_empty()\n                .with_service_name(\"git-fs\")\n                .build(),\n        )\n        .build();\n    let tracer = provider.tracer(\"git-fs\");\n    let otel_layer = tracing_opentelemetry::layer().with_tracer(tracer);\n\n    tracing_subscriber::registry()\n        .with(reload_layer)\n        .with(otel_layer)\n        .with(self.env_filter)\n        .try_init()?;\n\n    tracer_provider = Some(provider);\n}\n```\n\nThe 丑 branch stays the same, with `tracer_provider = None`.\n\n### 3. No changes to `main.rs`\n\n`TrcHandle` is already held for the lifetime of the program and dropped on exit. The `Drop` impl calls `provider.shutdown()` which flushes all pending spans to Jaeger.\n\n## Verification\n\n```\ncargo fmt --all && cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings && cargo test --quiet\n```\n\nManual test:\n1. Start Jaeger: `docker run -d --name jaeger -p 16686:16686 -p 4317:4317 jaegertracing/all-in-one:latest`\n2. Run with debug logging: `GIT_FS_LOG=debug cargo run -- run`\n3. Open http://localhost:16686, select service \"git-fs\", verify traces show spans like `OrgFs::lookup`, `RepoFs::readdir` with durations\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/marko/.claude/projects/-Users-marko-Desktop-gitfs-git-fs/c10bbe73-783d-48ce-a7f1-cd06ffe97645.jsonl","tools":{"read":1},"duration":27},{"id":69,"timestamp":"2026-02-10T23:42:43.952Z","content":"Base directory for this skill: /Users/marko/.claude/plugins/cache/superpowers-marketplace/superpowers/4.1.1/skills/executi